src_text: Seakanywa sa Melao ya Lefapha la Semolao (Seakanywa sa LSC) Kabinete e dumelet we go phatlalat wa ga Seakanywa sa LSC gore set haba se fe ditshwayotshwayo t a son Dinepo t a melao ye ke go kgont ha diphetogo ka lefapheng la semolao go fihlelela tekatekano ya batho goya le ka dipalopalo t a ka mo nagen Melao ye e tla netefat a gape le gore go ba le setheo seo se tla t welet ago baabaditirelo bao ba hlahlilwego gabotse le ba bokgoni ditirelong t a semola Go hlangwa ga Seakanywa se sa LSC go lekot we ke Khansele ya Phethagat o ya Semolao e bago setheo sa mmu o seo se hlamilwego goya ka Karolo 4 ya Molao wa Phethagat o ya Semolao, 2014 (Molao 28 wa 2014) le go hlahlwa ke Molao wa Matlafat o ya Ikonomi ya Bathobaso yeo e Nabilego (B-BBEE), 2013 (Molao 46 wa 2013).
trg_text: Draft Legal Sector Code (Draft LSC) Cabinet approved the publication of the Draft LSC for public commen The objectives of these codes are to facilitate the transformation of the legal sector to achieve representation as per the country s demographic The code will also ensure the development of the body that will produce well-trained and competent providers of legal service The development of the Draft LSC was overseen by the Legal Practice Council, a statutory body established in terms of Section 4 of the Legal Practice Act, 2014 (Act 28 of 2014) and guided by the Broad-Based Black Economic Empowerment Act (B-BBEE), 2013 (Act 46 of 2013).

src_text: Molao wa B-BBEE wa 2013 o bolela ka gore Tona ya Dikgwebi ano, Diintasteri le Diphenkgi ano o tla lokolla ditlhathollo t a phethagat o ye maleba matlafat ong ya ikonomi ya bathobaso mo mafapheng a go ikgeth Maloko a profe ene ya semolao ka motsotso wo ga ba na melao ya lefapha le ya go ba hlahla go kalokana le go fetafetana le go se lekalekane profe eneng ya semola Seakanywa sa LSC se tlo phatlalat wa ka gare ga Kuranta ya Mmu o mo mat at ing a 60 go dumelela set haba go fa ditshwayotshwayo t a son 2.
trg_text: The B-BBEE Act of 2013 provides for the Minister of Trade, Industry and Competition to issue codes of good practice on black economic empowerment in the specific sector Members of the legal profession currently do not have a sector code to guide them in addressing the imbalances and inequalities in the legal professio The Draft LSC will be published in the Government Gazette for 60 days to allow for public comment 2.
